article.headline: Stony Brook 82, Fairleigh Dickinson 58
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Mike Popoko scored 17 of his 21 points in the first half to lead Stony Brook to an 82-58 victory over Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday. Ricky Lucas added 18 points for the Seawolves (5-6). Andre Harris scored 20 points to lead the Knights (5-4). Popoko, who finished 9-for-15 from the field, scored seven points in a 20-9 run that gave Stony Brook its largest lead of the first half, 44-28 with 1:49 to go. The Seawolves, who opened the game with a 15-2 run, led 48-31 at halftime. A jumper by Michael Peeples with 13:26 to play brought Fairleigh Dickinson within 56-45, but that was as close as the Knights would get.
